12 Article to read:
13 "Article 1B.
14 "Redistricting.
15 "§ 120-4.50. Definitions.
16 As used in this Article, unless the context requires otherwise, the following definitions shall
17 apply:
18 (1) Census Bureau. – The United States Bureau of the Census.
19 (2) Commission. – The North Carolina Independent Redistricting Commission
20 established pursuant to G.S. 120-4.55.
21 (3) Communities of interest. – An area or population with recognized similarities
22 of interest, including racial, ethnic, economic, social, cultural, geographic, and
23 historical identities. Communities of interest do not include common
24 relationships with political parties or political candidates. Examples of
25 communities of interest may include municipalities, neighborhoods, and
26 census designated places.
27 (4) Congressional districts or plans. – Districts or plans for the House of
28 Representatives of the United States Congress.
29 (5) Federal decennial census. – The decennial census required by federal law to
30 be conducted by the Census Bureau in every year ending in zero.
31 (6) Final plan. – A plan adopted by the Commission to be used for the purpose of
32 nominating and electing identified representatives. In accordance with Section
33 25 of Article II of the North Carolina Constitution, final plans shall have the
34 force and effect of acts of the General Assembly.
35 (7) Ideal population. – The number determined by dividing the number of
36 members in a plan into the population of the State as reported in the federal
37 census.
38 (8) Identified representative. – A member of the Senate or the House of
39 Representatives of the General Assembly or a member of the House of
40 Representatives of the United States Congress.
41 (9) Indigenous person. – A member of a federal or State-recognized Indian tribe.
42 (10) Legislative districts or plans. – Districts or plans for the Senate and the House
43 of Representatives of the General Assembly.
44 (11) Metropolitan or micropolitan statistical areas. – Areas of the State defined as
45 metropolitan or micropolitan statistical areas by the Office of Management
46 and Budget of the United States.
47 (12) Plan. – A plan for legislative or congressional reapportionment drawn in
48 accordance with Section 25 of Article II of the North Carolina Constitution
49 and this Article.
50 (13) Preliminary plan. – An initial plan released by the Commission for public
51 input at the beginning of the redistricting cycle.
