6 (e) Term of Office. – The term of office for members of the Commission shall begin on
7 July 1 of each year ending in zero. The members shall continue in office for 10 years until their
8 successors are appointed and qualified.
9 (f) Chair. – The position of chair of the Commission shall rotate every three months,
10 following a schedule randomly generated at the beginning of the redistricting cycle. No two
11 members who share the same party affiliation, or lack thereof, shall serve as chair in the same
12 six-month period. No member shall serve as chair more than once in a 12-month period.
13 (g) Removal from Office. – A member of the Commission may be removed from office,
14 as follows:
15 (1) By the authority that appointed the member for any of the following:
16 a. Failure to comply with G.S. 120-4.65.
17 b. Ineligibility pursuant to subsection (b) of this section.
18 (2) By a vote of at least 11 members of the Commission, including at least one
19 member of the commission who shares the same party affiliation, or lack
20 thereof, in open session at any duly held meeting, for any cause that renders
21 the member incapable or unfit to discharge the duties of the office, including
22 neglect of duty or gross misconduct. All Commission member votes on
23 removal of a member pursuant to this subdivision shall be recorded.
24 (h) Vacancies. – Any vacancy occurring in the membership of the Commission shall be
25 filled in the manner prescribed in this section by the authority that made the initial appointment.
26 Vacancies shall be filled for the remainder of the unexpired term.
27 (i) Prohibition on Legislative Service. – No member of the Commission shall serve as a
28 member of the General Assembly or Congress until the conclusion of the term as a commissioner
29 that they were appointed to serve. This prohibition applies even if a commissioner resigns or is
30 removed from the Commission prior to the conclusion of his or her term.
31 (j) Stipend. – Members of the Commission shall receive a stipend of two thousand
32 dollars ($2,000) for each month that the Commission meets.
33 (k) Other Expenses. – Members of the Commission may receive travel and subsistence,
34 as follows:
35 (1) Members who are officials or employees of a State agency or unit of local
36 government, in accordance with G.S. 138-6.
37 (2) All other members at the rate established in G.S. 138-5.
38 "§ 120-4.60. Staff.
39 (a) The Commission shall be administratively housed in the Legislative Services Office
40 of the General Assembly.
41 (b) The Commission may exercise its prescribed powers independently of the General
42 Assembly and the Legislative Services Officer. In order to pay expenses incidental to
43 implementing its purposes, the Commission may enter into contracts, own property, and accept
44 funds, grants, and gifts from academic and nonprofit entities that have never contributed to
45 political parties, persons holding public office, or candidates for public office.
46 (c) The Legislative Services Officer shall provide general administrative support to the
47 Commission, including purchasing, payroll, and similar administrative services.
48 (d) The Commission shall retain independent staff under contract, including an executive
49 secretary and any additional necessary supporting staff. As a whole, the political affiliations of
50 staff members, or lack thereof, shall be divided approximately into thirds among the two political
51 parties with the highest number of affiliates and among persons unaffiliated with a political party.
