1 (1) Sufficient time to review any plan released to the public in advance of any
2 vote on that plan.
3 (2) The opportunity to communicate comments, questions, and recommendations
4 on any plan released to the public, at a minimum, in person, online, and
5 through the mail. The Commission shall reserve time at the end of every
6 meeting for in-person and virtual public comment.
7 (3) Access to the same demographic data that is used by the Commission in a
8 machine-readable form.
9 (4) Access to mapping software and census data in public library facilities in each
