19 a. The impact of the plans on the ability of minority groups, including
20 racial minorities, to elect candidates of their choice.
21 b. The degree to which the plans preserve or divide communities of
22 interest.
23 c. The rationale for changes in the plans from the prior districts.
24 d. The impact of the plans on metropolitan and micropolitan statistical
25 areas.
26 e. How the plans satisfy the redistricting criteria in G.S. 120-4.70.
27 f. A summary of the public input received by the Commission on the
28 plans. Substantially similar comments may be grouped together into
29 categories.
30 (7) A website with all of the following information:
31 a. Background information on the redistricting process available in at
